Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Sudan. The Sudanese authorities have suspended all international commercial passenger flights to and from Sudan.
The Sudanese authorities have closed all land borders (except for transfer of humanitarian aid).
We know this is concerning for British people trying to leave Sudan. The UK government is working closely with airlines, the Sudanese authorities and other governments to make sure options are available for you to return to the UK as soon as possible.
What to do
If you are a British national in Sudan and wish to register your intention to return to the UK, please email the details listed below to our dedicated mailbox at stayincontactsudan@fco.gov.uk. Please register your details with us even if you have previously been in contact so that we have the information listed below:
Your full name as shown on your passport
Passport number
Date of birth
Place of residence in UK
Where exactly you are currently staying in Sudan
Email address and telephone number (please ensure that you are able to receive phone calls from unidentified numbers, including internationally, in case we need to reach you)
Any specific medical needs/vulnerabilities
Evidence of your return journey to the UK, eg an itinerary or confirmed flight booking that you were unable to use or is imminent.
Copy of the details page of your passport
Please provide the information requested above for any family members with you in Sudan that are also seeking to return to the UK.
If you cannot leave Sudan at this time, you should:
Follow the advice of the Sudanese authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus.
Find accommodation thatâ€™s suitable for your needs.
Keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well
See more information and advice about staying where you are if you cannot return to the UK
Future travel options
The UK government is working closely with airlines, the Sudanese authorities and other governments to make sure options are available for you to return to the UK as soon as possible.
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy Facebook and Twitter.
You will need to pay for return travel to the UK. If departure options become available but you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information see the guidance on financial assistance while you are abroad.
Help and Support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy on +249 156 77 55 00.
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available and, if you are registered with the Embassy, we will alert you by email. To get the latest information sign up for travel advice email alerts.
Your journey home
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air. When you arrive back in the UK, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others.
Further information
See more information and advice about staying where you are if you cannot return to the UK.
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
